InclusionRules.name: Use of the following excluded medications: pitaglitazone
No current CV event
InclusionRules.description:
Acute cardiovascular event
[e.g., acute coronary syndrome (ACS), transient ischemic attack (TIA), stroke, any revascularization, decompensated HF(heart failure), sustained tachycardia <8 weeks prior to randomization.

InclusionRules.name: No history of bladdercancer or radiation therapy to the lower abdomen or pelvis at any time
No history of cancer
InclusionRules.description: History of any other malignancy within 5 years (with the exception of successfully treated non-melanoma skin cancers)

InclusionRules.name: No chronic cystitis / recurrent UTI
InclusionRules.description: Chronic cystitis and/or recurrent urinary tract infections (3 or more in the last year)

InclusionRules.name: No AST or ALT >3x ULN or Total bilirubin >2.5 x ULN
No CrCl < 60 ml/min (based on the Cockroft-Gault equation)
No hematuria
InclusionRules.description: Hematuria (confirmed by microscopy at Visit 1) with no explanation as judged by the Investigator up to randomization. If bladder cancer is identified, patients are not eligible to participate.

InclusionRules.name: Any conditions that, in the opinion of the Investigator, may render the patient unable to complete the study including but not limited to cardiovascular (NYHA class IV CHF, recurrent ventricular arrhythmias)  or non-cardiovascular disease

Involvement in the planning and/or conduct of the study or other dapagliflozin studies (applies to AZ, BMS, Hadassah and Thrombolysis in Myocardial Infarction [TIMI] or representative staff and/or staff at the study site)
Active participation in another clinical study with IP and/or investigational device

Individuals at risk for poor protocol or medication compliance during run-in period(reasonable compliance defined as 80 <U+2013> 120%, unless a reason for non-compliance is judged acceptable by the Investigator).  If for any reason, the Investigator believes tha
Any reason the Investigator believes the patient is not likely to be compliant with the study medication and protocol.
Systolic BP >180 or diastolic BP >100 mmHg at randomization
